{
  "texts": [
    "Mutual Information (MI) measures the amount of information shared between the cluster and its main topic.",
    "This study identifies different research trends and technological development of Doubly Fed Induction Generators (DFIG) in Wind Energy Conversion Systems (WECS) using the clustering approach.",
    "Some initial clusters like cluster 8 and 9 that deals with reactive power control and Dynamic performance of DFIGs are part of the basic research carried out in the late nineties.",
    "These studies provided the basis for studying the behaviour and control of DFIG based wind turbines during operation.",
    "The new clusters, such as Cluster 2 and Cluster 5, identify the relatively recent developments in adaptive control algorithms and nonlinear feedback control methods, which enhance the stability and performance of DFIG systems in the contemporary variable speed wind power applications."
  ]
}